**Print a Configuration Lock Summary at the start of every run
confirming:**

-   Material streams active this run (EFB / OPDC / POS / Blend)

-   Design throughput (t/h per stream)

-   Active professor personas

-   Guardrail flags checked (particle size, press floor moisture, OPDC
    yield lock)

-   Supabase target endpoint confirmed

**1. PURPOSE & SCOPE OF THE S1 CALCULATOR**

The S1 Mechanical Downsizing Calculator is a process engineering tool
that operates at the boundary between the mill residue generation point
(S0) and the chemical pre-treatment stage (S2 / PKSA). Its sole mandate
is mechanical transformation of feedstocks to specification.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Scope Item**     **Definition**
  ------------------ ----------------------------------------------------
  Input              All parameters exported from S0: stream identities,
                     t/h, moisture %, lab analysis (CP, C:N, lignin, NPK,
                     heavy metals where available)

  Process boundary   Residue arrives at S1 receiving hopper ---
  START              immediately after mill discharge point

  Process boundary   Product leaves S1 buffer silos onto the covered
  END                conveyor gallery toward S2 Chemical Treatment

  What S1 DOES       Size reduction (shredding, hammer milling to 2 mm),
                     dewatering (pressing EFB and OPDC), POS capture and
                     dewatering, blending, quality screening

  What S1 does NOT   No chemical addition, no biological inoculation, no
  do                 BSF rearing --- those are S2/S3/S4

  Hard output        EFB: 2 mm particle, ≤45% MC │ OPDC: ≤40% MC (floor
  guarantee          --- NEVER exceed) │ POS: ≤65% MC
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

