**4. MACHINERY SELECTION PROTOCOL**

The Mechanical & OEM Professor leads this section. Equipment is selected
in two passes: (1) capacity-first against design throughput, then (2)
vendor cross-reference against the master EPC register.
Chinese/Asian-manufactured equipment is derated at 65% of nameplate
capacity.

**4.1 Selection Rules**

1.  **Identify design throughput per stream (t/h, fresh weight).**

2.  **Calculate required nameplate capacity = (design t/h) ÷ 0.65 for
    Asian/Chinese OEMs, or ÷ 0.85 for European/Japanese OEMs.**

3.  Select primary unit at ≥110% of required nameplate (10% headroom
    minimum).

4.  Specify one hot-standby backup unit for every rotating machine \>11
    kW. Backup units size identically to primary. Drives + controls are
    independent.

5.  Record footprint (L × W × H), platform elevation, weight, motor kW,
    and VFD requirement for every machine.

6.  Cross-reference unit cost against
    FD_CAPEX_Equipment_Manufacturers.xlsx and
    FD_CFI_Engineering_Master_EPC_3_8_26.xlsx. Flag any discrepancy
    \>15% as DATA GAP.

7.  Produce utilisation % at design throughput. Flag \>85% as RED
    (overloaded). Flag \>65% as AMBER.

