**8. S1 END-OF-PROCESS LAB ANALYSIS OUTPUT**

The Environmental Chemistry & Lab Professor (#23) governs this section.
The S1 lab analysis packet is generated at the process boundary ---
immediately before material enters the conveyor gallery to S2. It
confirms that mechanical treatment has achieved specification.

**8.1 S1 Lab Analysis Packet --- Required Parameters**

  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Test**      **Stream**   **Method**     **Target / Guardrail**    **Lab
                                                                      Package**
  ------------- ------------ -------------- ------------------------- -----------
  Moisture      EFB, OPDC,   Gravimetric    EFB ≤45% │ OPDC ≤40%      C
  content       POS          105°C          (FLOOR) │ POS ≤65%        

  Particle size EFB only     Sieve analysis D90 ≤ 2 mm (LOCKED)       C
  D90                                                                 

  Crude protein EFB, OPDC,   Kjeldahl (N ×  EFB 4.75 │ OPDC 14.5 │    B
  % DM          POS          4.67)          POS \~11.0                

  Ash % DM      All streams  Muffle 550°C   POS \~28% DM (guardrail)  C

  Total N % DM  All streams  Kjeldahl /     EFB \~0.76 │ OPDC \~2.3 │ B
                             Dumas          POS \~1.76                

  Total P % DM  All streams  ICP-OES        As per S0 baseline        A

  Total K % DM  All streams  ICP-OES        As per S0 baseline        A

  pH            POS, Blend   pH meter       POS: verify range         C
                sample       slurry 1:5                               

  Ether Extract POS only     Soxhlet        \~10% DM (Feedipedia      C
  % DM                                      29.2% REJECTED)           

  Fe mg/kg DM   POS only     ICP-OES        \<3,000 → 20% WW          A
                                            inclusion │ 3,000--5,000  
                                            → 10--15% │ \>8,000 →     
                                            CaCO₃                     

  Mn mg/kg DM   POS only     ICP-OES        100--475 mg/kg DM typical A

  C:N ratio     Blend sample TOC+Kjeldahl   Blend target \~32         C
                                            (DM-weighted formula)     
  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------

> **⚠ 3-DAY REPLICATE SAMPLING RULE (CFI-LAB-POME-001): Collect samples
> on three independent days before treating S1 lab output as confirmed.
> Single-day results may be used for real-time process control only.**
>
> **⚠ RECOMMENDED LABS: Balai Penelitian Tanah Bogor │ Eurofins
> Indonesia │ Sucofindo. Do not use labs without ISO 17025 accreditation
> for ICP-OES packages.**

**9. SUPABASE DATA ARCHITECTURE & WRITE INSTRUCTIONS**

The MRV & Technology Professor (#30) governs this section. Every
completed S1 run writes a record to the s1_run_log table. The s2_payload
JSONB column carries the full handoff to S2. The NPK relay is also
written here for downstream NPK Calculator pickup.

**9.1 Supabase Connection**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Parameter**   **Value**
  --------------- -------------------------------------------------------
  Project URL     https://lcpbtnipkvrmuwllymfw.supabase.co

  Target table    s1_run_log

  Auth method     anon key (hardcoded in app) --- never expose in
                  client-side logs

  Write trigger   On completion of each S1 run or shift-end summary
                  (operator confirmation required)

  Read by         S2 Chemical Treatment Calculator │ NPK Value Dashboard
                  │ Plantation Intelligence Tab
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**9.2 SQL Schema --- s1_run_log**

> \-- TABLE: s1_run_log
>
> CREATE TABLE s1_run_log (
>
> id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
>
> run_ts TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
>
> mill_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT \'BOGOR-60TPH\',
>
> ffb_tph NUMERIC(8,3), \-- FFB throughput t/h
>
> efb_tph NUMERIC(8,3), \-- EFB t/h from S0
>
> opdc_tph NUMERIC(8,3), \-- OPDC t/h from S0
>
> pos_tph NUMERIC(8,3), \-- POS t/h from S0
>
> \-- S1 OUTPUTS
>
> efb_out_tph NUMERIC(8,3), \-- EFB post-mill, 2mm, 45% MC
>
> opdc_out_tph NUMERIC(8,3), \-- OPDC post-press, 40% MC
>
> pos_out_tph NUMERIC(8,3), \-- POS post-dewater, 65% MC
>
> blend_tpd NUMERIC(10,3), \-- Combined blend t/day
>
> \-- EQUIPMENT HEALTH
>
> efb_press_util_pct NUMERIC(5,2),
>
> opdc_press_util_pct NUMERIC(5,2),
>
> hammer_util_pct NUMERIC(5,2),
>
> \-- LAB ANALYSIS PACKET (S1 end-of-process)
>
> efb_mc_out_pct NUMERIC(5,2),
>
> efb_cp_pct_dm NUMERIC(5,2),
>
> efb_cn_ratio NUMERIC(6,2),
>
> efb_lignin_pct NUMERIC(5,2),
>
> opdc_mc_out_pct NUMERIC(5,2),
>
> opdc_cp_pct_dm NUMERIC(5,2),
>
> opdc_cn_ratio NUMERIC(6,2),
>
> pos_mc_out_pct NUMERIC(5,2),
>
> pos_cp_pct_dm NUMERIC(5,2),
>
> \-- NPK RELAY
>
> blend_n_kgd NUMERIC(8,2),
>
> blend_p_kgd NUMERIC(8,2),
>
> blend_k_kgd NUMERIC(8,2),
>
> \-- CAPEX SNAPSHOT
>
