**13. MULTI-PROMPT vs. SINGLE-PROMPT ARCHITECTURE**

To answer your explicit question: YES, S1 can and should be split into
several prompts for production deployment. The recommended decomposition
is:

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Sub-Prompt**   **Name**        **Trigger        **Output**
                                   Condition**      
  ---------------- --------------- ---------------- ---------------------------------
  S1-A             S0 Data Import  New S0 data      Validated input object + DATA GAP
                   & Validation    batch arrives    list

  S1-B             Machinery       On commissioning Equipment register + utilisation
                   Selection &     or design change table
                   Sizing                           

  S1-C             Real-Time Mass  Every operating  Stream outputs, moisture checks,
                   Balance         shift            blend composition
                   Calculator                       

  S1-D             CAPEX / OPEX    On design change Full cost tables for CFO
                   Generator       or quarterly     
                                   review           

  S1-E             Lab Analysis    On lab results   S1-LAB-xxxx packet + guardrail
                   Output          receipt          gate check
                   Processor                        

  S1-F             Supabase        End of every     Database write + s2_payload + NPK
                   Writer + S2     shift / run      relay
                   Handoff                          
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This master prompt encompasses ALL of the above. When deploying as
separate prompts, each sub-prompt should include Section 0 (Governing
Documents) and reference this master document by version.

